tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, low total CO₂, and significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity. These findings suggest impaired renal function, possible metabolic acidosis, and abnormal glucose handling despite low HbA1c. Urine abnormalities (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal) further support renal involvement. Recommend urgent clinical evaluation for possible acute or chronic kidney disease and metabolic derangements.
